The Kilometre Zero monument (Romanian: Kilometrul Zero) located in central Bucharest, Romania, in front of Saint George's Church, was created by  in 1938.

The distances from Bucharest to other cities in Romania are measured from this monument. It is divided into eight sections, each representing a Romanian historical province: Muntenia, , Bessarabia, Moldavia, , Transylvania, Banat and Oltenia. Among the cities inscribed on it are also , Orhei, Tighina, which are currently in the , as well as Silistra and Dobrich (Bazargic) in Bulgaria, which were part of Greater Romania
